Reader, here you'l plainly see iudgement perverted by these three, a priest, a judge, a patentee written by Thomas Heywood. Heywood, Thomas, d. 1641.
[2], 6 p.
s.n.], [London : 1641.
Illustration (wood-cut) on t.p., representing the three characters (i.e. Archbishop Laud, Lord keeper Finch, and Alderman Abell). Caption title: Bishops, iudges, monopolists. In verse. Reproduction of original in Huntington Library.
